|{{flag|Armenia}}||1994-07-08||See [[Armenia–Croatia relations]]
* Armenia is represented in Croatia through its non-resident ambassador based in the Armenian embassy in [[Athens]] ([[Greece]]).
* Croatia is represented in Armenia through its non-resident ambassador based in the Croatian embassy in Athens (Greece).
* [http://www.mvpei.hr/CustomPages/Static/HRV//templates/_frt_bilateralni_odnosi_po_drzavama_en.asp?id=53  Croatian Ministry of Foreign Affairs: list of bilateral treaties with Armenia]
|- valign=&quot;top&quot;
|{{flag|Bahrain}}||1993-01-18||
|- valign=&quot;top&quot;
|{{flag|Iran}}||1992-04-18||See [[Croatia–Iran relations]]

Both countries established diplomatic relations on April 18, 1992 when Iran became the 7th country to recognize the newly-independent Croatia. Croatia has an embassy in Tehran and Iran maintains an embassy and a cultural centre in Zagreb.
