|{{Flag|Norway }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;||See [[Cyprus-Norway relations]]

'''Cyprus-Norway relations''' are foreign relations between [[Cyprus]] and [[Norway]]. Diplomatic relations were established on March 22, 1963.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/All/4FC761EE2A113ECBC22571E1002F4D22/$file/Norway.pdf?OpenElement |title=Kingdom of Norway |accessdate=2010-05-15 |quote= |publisher=[[Cyprus]] }}&lt;/ref&gt; The government in Cyprus considers that &quot;bilateral relations between Cyprus and Norway are excellent in all fields&quot;.&lt;ref name=&quot;Cyprus Embassy&quot;/&gt;

Neither country has resident ambassadors. Cyprus is represented in Norway through its embassy in [[Stockholm, Sweden]] and 2 honorary consulates, one in [[Oslo]] and the second in [[Kristiansand]]. Norway is represented in Cyprus through its embassy in [[Athens, Greece]] and an honorary consulate in [[Nicosia]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.norway.gr/Embassy/Consulates/ |title=Consulates in Greece and Cyprus |accessdate=2010-05-15 |quote=There are several Norwegian Honorary Consulates in Greece, and one in Nicosia, Cyprus. |publisher=[[Norway]] }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}&lt;/ref&gt; Both countries are full members of the [[Council of Europe]]. Diplomatic relations were established on 22 March 1963.&lt;ref name=&quot;Cyprus Embassy&quot;&gt;{{Cite web
|url=http://www.cyprusemb.se/dbase/cypemb/3_political_section_norway.asp
|title=Cyprus – Norway Bilateral Relations
|publisher= [[Cyprus|Embassy of Cyprus in Sweden]]
|accessdate=May 03, 2009
}}&lt;/ref&gt;

On August 21, 1951 there was a Consular Convention and an Exchange of Letters relating to establishing diplomatic relations. On May 2, 1951 there was a [[Convention for the Avoidance of Double Taxation]] and the Prevention of Fiscal Evasion with respect to Taxes on Income. On May 17, 1962 there was an Exchange of Letters constituting an [[Visa requirements for Northern Cypriot citizens|Agreement on the Abolition of Visa Requirement]] in [[Nicosia]]. On March 5, 1963 there was an Agreement on Commercial Scheduled Air Transport signed in [[London]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/All/4FC761EE2A113ECBC22571E1002F4D22/$file/Norway.pdf%3FOpenElement |title=Kingdom of Norway |accessdate=2010-05-21 |quote= |publisher=[[Cyprus]] }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}&lt;/ref&gt;

Norway provides direct funding to the Cypriot Government and also to local authorities, NGOs and educational institutions through [[EEA and Norway Grants]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite news|author= |coauthors= |title=Norwegian partners get valuable insight in Cyprus |url=http://www.norway.gr/News_and_events/business_and_eea/eea/Norwegian-partners-get-valuable-insight-in-Cyprus/ |quote= |work=[[Norway|Royal Norwegian Embassy in Athens]] |year=2008 |accessdate=2010-05-15 }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}&lt;/ref&gt; The NGO Fund in Cyprus is co-financed by the [[European Economic Area]] (EEA) Financial Mechanism and the Norwegian Financial Mechanism. It was established in 2004.&lt;ref name=ngo/&gt; In 2006, Norway increased its commitment to offer a total contribution of 4.66 million [[euro]]s.&lt;ref name=ngo&gt;{{Cite web
|url=http://www.eeangofund.org.cy/page_1229620162754.html
|title=NGO Fund Launch Event
|work= The Fund for Non Governmental Organisations in Cyprus
|accessdate=May 01, 2009
}}&lt;/ref&gt; In 2007 a delegation from the [[EEA and Norway Grants]] went to Cyprus to &quot;monitor the spending of Norwegian funds given to Cyprus as part of the [[European Economic Area]].&quot;&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite news|author= |coauthors= |title=Norway allocates 4.7 million euro to Cyprus |url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NewsLibrary&amp;p_multi=BBAB&amp;d_place=BBAB&amp;p_theme=newslibrary2&amp;p_action=search&amp;p_maxdocs=200&amp;p_topdoc=1&amp;p_text_direct-0=11CEB9D290E2C8D0&amp;p_field_direct-0=document_id&amp;p_perpage=10&amp;p_sort=YMD_date:D&amp;s_trackval=GooglePM |quote=A delegation of the Norwegian EEA Financial Mechanism is on the island to monitor the spending of Norwegian funds given to Cyprus as part of the European Economic Area Agreement. A meeting on this issue was held at the Planning Bureau between the Norwegian delegation and a Cypriot ... |work=[[Cyprus News Agency]] |date= November 13, 2007  |accessdate=2010-05-16 }}&lt;/ref&gt; In 2008 Norwegian Foreign Minister [[Jonas Gahr Støre]] traveled to Cyprus to meet President [[Demetris Christofias]]. They met to discuss Norway's assistance to the Cypriot village of [[Salamiou]], in [[Paphos]]. The Norwegians plan to rebuild an old elementary school in the village. It will then become a Regional Centre for Environmental Education at the cost of [[€]] 735,000.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite news|author= |coauthors= |title=Norway’s FM visits to inaugurate environmental project |url=http://www.cyprus-mail.com/cyprus/norway-s-fm-visits-inaugurate-environmental-project |quote= |work=[[Cyprus Mail]] |date=June 29, 2008 |accessdate=2010-05-21 }}&lt;/ref&gt;

The taxation levels in Cyprus are considerably lower than in Norway, and Cyprus has actively courted Norwegians to move to Cyprus.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite news|url=http://www.dagsavisen.no/innenriks/article266870.ece|title=Kypros jakter på rike nordmenn|date=May 11, 2006|quote=Det ble i går kjent at skipsreder John Fredriksen tidligere Norges rikeste mann har gitt opp sitt norske pass og blitt kypriot. Fredriksen kom dermed kypriotene i forkjøpet.|language=Norwegian | work=[[Dagsavisen]]|accessdate=2009-05-06}}&lt;/ref&gt; Among the Norwegians who moved to Cyprus is the shipping billionaire [[John Fredriksen]], who was the richest man in Norway.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite news|author= |coauthors= |title=Norway's richest man no longer |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/english/business/article1314163.ece |quote= |work=[[Aftenposten]] |date=May 11, 2006 |accessdate=2010-05-15 }}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite news|author= |coauthors= |title=Skatteflyktet til Kypros |url=http://www.ukeavisenledelse.no/arkiv/skatteflyktet_til_kypros?utskrift=1 |quote=Norges rikeste mann, god for minst 33 milliarder kroner, John Fredriksen (61), har gitt opp sitt norske statsborgerskap og allerede fått innvilget kypriotisk – av skattemessige årsaker. |work=Ukeavisenledelse|language=Norwegian |date=August 23, 2006 |accessdate=2010-05-15 }}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite news|url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/article1311458.ece|title=Fredriksen blir kypriot|language=Norwegian |date=May 10, 2006|work=[[Aftenposten]]|accessdate=2009-05-06}}&lt;/ref&gt;

In 1996 tax rules in Norway were changed to keep shipping companies competitive and under the Norwegian flag. By 2008 changes to the tonnage tax regime to harmonize them with the [[European Union]] forced some companies to register in Cyprus.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite news|author= |coauthors= |title=Norway's Whilhelmsen moving shipping unit to Malta |url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/idUKL1860840120080618 |quote=The changes were aimed at making Norwegian shipping rules more like those in the European Union, but industry groups have said the move might force some to register in tax havens such as Bermuda or Cyprus. |work=[[Reuters]] |date=June 18, 2008 |accessdate=2010-05-15 }}&lt;/ref&gt; Norwegian [[Service rig]] company [[Prosafe]] moved their headquarters to Cyprus.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite news|language=Norwegian|url=http://e24.no/boers-og-finans/article1635271.ece|title=Rømmer norsk utbytteskatt|date=February 9, 2007|work=[[E24 Næringsliv]]|accessdate=2009-05-06}}&lt;/ref&gt;

Several Norwegian retirees also moved to Cyprus; this too is largely to benefit from the lower tax rate on Cyprus and the minimal crime.&lt;ref name=home&gt;{{Cite news|author= |coauthors= |title=Cyprus is surging forward with state-of-the-art homes |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/property/article-1168822/Get-ahead-Med-Cyprus-surging-forward-state-art-homes.html#ixzz0oWXCYdZ6 |quote=What's more, since Norway's richest man, John Fredriksen, took Cypriot citizenship in 2006, the flow of his fellow countrymen has increased, too, with investors taking advantage of the lowest income tax in Europe and minimal crime rates.  |work=[[Daily Mail]] |date=April 9, 2009 |accessdate=2010-05-21 | location=London | first=Liz | last=Rowlinson}}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name=colony/&gt; The Norwegian colony on Cyprus is in [[Paphos]].&lt;ref name=colony&gt;{{Cite news|url=http://www.vg.no/dinepenger/artikkel.php?artid=544780|quote=Low taxation, low living costs and summery winter temperature limits more and more Norwegians to settle on the Mediterranean island. Now we have established a Norwegian &quot;colony&quot; in Paphos in Cyprus similar seen in Spain. |title=Norske pensjonister: Flytter til 8% skatt på Kypros |date=December 4, 2008|work=[[Verdens Gang|VG Nett]]|accessdate=2009-05-06}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/All/4FC761EE2A113ECBC22571E1002F4D22/$file/Norway.pdf?OpenElement   Cyprus Ministry of Foreign Affairs: list of bilateral treaties with Norway]
* [http://www.cyprusemb.se/dbase/cypemb/default.asp  Cyprus embassy in Stockholm (also accredted to Norway)]
* [http://www.norway.gr/  Norway embassy in Athens (also accredited to Cyprus)]
|--valign=&quot;top&quot;
|{{Flag|Poland }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;1960s||See [[Cyprus–Poland relations]]

* Cyprus has an embassy in [[Warsaw]] and 2 honorary consulates (in [[Gdynia]] and [[Szczecin]]).
* Poland has an embassy in [[Nicosia]] and an honorary consulate general in [[Limassol]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.nikozja.polemb.net/  Polish embassy in Nicosia]&lt;/ref&gt;
* Both countries are full members of the [[European Union]].
* [http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/All/BEE553894C1C0963C22571E10034714C/$file/Poland.pdf?OpenElement  Cyprus Foreign Affairs: List of bilateral treaties with Poland]
|--valign=&quot;top&quot;
