* India has a High Commission in [[Nicosia]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.hcinicosia.org.cy/ Indian high commission in Nicosia]&lt;/ref&gt;
* Both countries are full members of the [[Commonwealth of Nations]].
* Cypriots are recognised as part of [[Greece]] by the Indians.
* [http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/All/210EAF74262E6F34C22571E100240EC8/$file/India.pdf?OpenElement  Cypriot Ministry of Foreign Affairs: list of bilateral treaties with India]
|--valign=&quot;top&quot;
|{{Flag|Japan }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;1962-06
|
* Cypriot president [[Makarios III|Makarios]] made a state visit to Japan in 1970. Subsequently Cypriot president [[Spyros Kyprianou]] visited in 1984 and president [[George Vasiliou]] visited in 1989 and 1990.
* The [[balance of trade]] between Cyprus and Japan is heavily weighed in favor of Japan, with Japan exporting automobiles and electrical products and importing clothing and food products.
* Cyprus is represented in Japan through its non-resident ambassador based in [[Beijing]], [[China]], with an [[honorary consulate]] in [[Tokyo]].
* Japan is represented in Cyprus through its non-resident ambassador based in [[Athens]], [[Greece]], with as an honorary consulate in [[Limassol]].
* [http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/All/DD14B376D1739554C22571E100267F32/$file/Japan.pdf?OpenElement  Cypriot Ministry of Foreign Affairs: list of bilateral treaties with Japan]
* [http://www.mofa.go.jp/region/europe/cyprus/index.html Japanese Ministry of Foreign Affairs on relations with Cyprus]
