==Overview==

The Republic of Cyprus maintains diplomatic relations with 177 states (including the [[Holy See]] and [[State of Palestine|Palestine]]) and is member of the [[European Union]]. It does not maintain diplomatic relations with:&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/policy02_en/policy02_en?OpenDocument Cyprus diplomatic relations]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/protocol04_en/protocol04_en?OpenDocument Cypriot diplomatic missions abroad]&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Monaco]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]], [[Azerbaijan]]
* [[Guinea-Bissau]], [[Togo]], [[Benin]], [[Republic of Congo]], [[Central African Republic]], [[Djibouti]]
* [[Bhutan]]
* [[Palau]], [[Kiribati]], [[Tuvalu]], [[Tonga]]
* [[Haiti]], [[Saint Kitts and Nevis]]
* [[Cook Islands]], [[Niue]]
* [[Sovereign Military Order of Malta]]
* [[Republic of Kosovo|Kosovo]], [[Abkhazia]], [[South Ossetia]], [[Somaliland]], [[Sahrawi Republic]], [[Nagorno-Karabakh Republic|Nagorno-Karabakh]], [[Republic of China (Taiwan)]], [[Transnistria]]
The Republic of Cyprus is not recognised by [[Turkey]] and the [[Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus]].

==Disputes - international==
[[File:Rice speaks with troops after landing in Larnaca July 24 2006.jpg|thumb|[[Condoleezza Rice]] by US ambassadors in [[Larnaca International Airport]], Cyprus]]
The 1974 invasion of the Turkish army divided the [[island nation]] into two. The internationally recognised Republic of Cyprus currently has effective control in the south of the island (59% of the island's land area) while its area not under its effective control makes up 37% of the island. Turkey utilising the territory occupied during the [[Turkish Invasion of Cyprus|invasion]] recognizes a declared [[separatism|separatist]]&lt;ref&gt;Christopher Hitchens, Uncorking the Genie: The Cyprus Question and Turkey's Military Rule MERIP Reports, No. 122, Turkey under Military Rule (Mar. - Apr., 1984), pp. 25-27, doi:10.2307/3011799&lt;/ref&gt; [[Declaration of Independence of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus|UDI]] of Turkish Cypriots in 1983, contrary to multiple United Nations Security Council Resolutions. The two territories of the Republic are separated by a [[United Nations Buffer Zone in Cyprus|United Nations Buffer Zone]] (4% of the island); there are two [[Sovereign Base Areas|UK sovereign base areas]] mostly within the Greek Cypriot portion of the island.

==Illicit drugs==
Cyprus is a minor transit point for [[heroin]] and [[hashish]] via air routes and container traffic to [[Europe]], especially from [[Lebanon]] and [[Turkey]]; some [[cocaine]] transits as well. The island has also been criticised for supposedly lax arms control legislation.

